  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a contributor, I want to have an easy way to get bootstrapped with the latest local build of status-react and status-go. Although the scenario has improved in recent weeks with the addition of [scripts/bundle-status-go.sh](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/blob/develop/scripts/bundle-status-go.sh), there's still room for improvement by wrapping the procedure in a Makefile target.\r\n\r\nIn the same vein, [scripts/setup.sh](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/blob/develop/scripts/setup.sh) can be exposed in the Makefile through a `make setup` target, giving it more visibility.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Feature\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what you expected to happen.)\r\nI'd like to be able to get the `status-react` and `status-go` repositories, set up the appropriate environment variables and then just run `make setup && make full-prod-build` to have a working status-react build for iOS and Android which uses the current `status-go` binaries that it just built on my machine.\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\n[comment]: # (Please summarise the solution and provide a task list on what needs to be fixed.)\r\n*Summary*: \r\n\r\n- [ ] Implement a `setup` target which calls `scripts/setup.sh`\r\n- [ ] Implement a `full-prod-build` target which calls `scripts/status-go.sh android` and `scripts/status-go.sh ios`, and then triggers the `prod-build` target.",
